<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="395" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,151,392]" pageId="1" pageNumber="395">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,332,357]" pageId="1" pageNumber="395">Etymology.</emphasis>
The genus name is based on the similarities with the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1911" box="[1051,1209,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Calamoncosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1051,1209,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="395">Calamoncosis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the additional prefix “ 
<emphasis box="[237,290,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="395">para</emphasis>
” derived from Greek, meaning similar.
</paragraph>
